<item>
            <title>[SOLR-11183] Prefix V2 APIs with /api</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-11183</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The mail thread&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://lucene.472066.n3.nabble.com/v2-API-will-there-ever-be-a-v3-td4340901.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://lucene.472066.n3.nabble.com/v2-API-will-there-ever-be-a-v3-td4340901.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;it makes sense to prefix v2 APIs at &lt;tt&gt;/api&lt;/tt&gt; intsead of &lt;tt&gt;/v2&lt;/tt&gt; if we never plan to have a &lt;tt&gt;/v3&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In principle, it makes total sense&lt;br/&gt;
The challenge is that it takes a while to change the code and tests to make to work. Should this be a blocker and should we hold up the release&lt;/p&gt;</description>
